1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact subdivision a of subsection 1 of section 53-06.1-03 of
2 the North Dakota Century Code, relating to the limitation on the value of a primary prize a
3 permitted organization conducting gaming may award.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Subdivision a of subsection 1 of section 53-06.1-03 of the
6 North Dakota Century Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
7 a. An organization recognized as a public-spirited organization by the governing
8 body of a city or county may apply for permits. A local permit may allow the
9 organization to conduct only raffles, bingo, or sports pools. A restricted event
10 permit may allow the organization to conduct only raffles, bingo, sports pools,
11 paddlewheels, twenty-one, and poker. The organization or closely related
12 organizations as a whole may only award a primary prize that does not exceed
13 eightfifteen thousand dollars and total prizes of all games do not exceed fortyfifty
14 thousand dollars per year. These maximum prize amounts do not apply to raffles
15 conducted under chapter 20.1-08. The determination of what is a "public-spirited
16 organization" is within the sole discretion of the governing body. An organization
17 shall disclose on the application its intended use of the net income from the
18 gaming activity. A governing body may issue a permit for games to be held at
19 designated times and places.
